model_explanation: the prosodic focus on "ELLEN" in S1 means Sam did not give bananas to anyone other than Ellen. This does not restrict what was given to Ellen. S2 says Sam also gave Ellen grapes, which contradicts the meaning of "only gave Ellen bananas," because that would mean she got only bananas and nothing else.

the prosodic focus on "MARY" means Sam didn’t give anyone else apples. It does not mean Mary got other items, only that no one else got apples. S2 says Sam didn’t give Mary oranges, which is consistent with S1. There is no contradiction. It is entailed that if Sam only gave Mary apples, this does not conflict with not giving her oranges.

the prosodic focus on "TOM" means the restriction is on who received bananas—only Tom. The sentence does not restrict what Tom received. S2 says Sam also gave Tom apples. This contradicts the meaning if the focus were on "bananas" (only bananas), but here the focus is on "TOM." Therefore, it contradicts the interpretation that Tom only got bananas and nothing else. The intended meaning matched a restriction on who got bananas, not what Tom got. But S2 directly contradicts the interpretation involving what Tom received when based on the common reading. Thus, the classification is contradiction.

the prosodic focus on "MARY" means the restriction is on the receiver of apples—only Mary got apples. It does not say anything about other items Mary might have gotten. S2 states Sam didn’t give Mary grapes. This is fully consistent with S1. There is no contradiction; it follows from S1 that nothing prohibits Mary from not getting grapes. It is entailed that Mary didn’t get other things, and it’s fully consistent. Therefore, it is entailed.

the prosodic focus is on "ORANGES"—this means Mary got only oranges from Sam and not any other type of fruit from Sam. S2 says Sam didn’t give Mary apples. This fits perfectly with the restriction provided by the prosodic focus in S1. Therefore, it is entailed.

the prosodic focus is on "APPLES"—this means that apples were only given to Rob and no one else got apples. S2 says Sam also gave Mary apples. That is independent and does not follow from S1. There is no logical contradiction or entailment; S2 is independent.

the prosodic focus is on "APPLES"—this means that apples were only given to Rob and no one else got apples. S2 says Sam also gave Tom apples, which contradicts the meaning of S1. It conflicts directly with the restriction that only Rob received apples.

the prosodic focus is on "ORANGES"—this means Rob got only oranges and not any other fruit. S2 says Sam didn’t give Rob bananas, which fits perfectly with the restriction in S1. It is entailed that Rob did not receive anything else besides oranges.

the prosodic focus is on "GRAPES"—this means grapes were only given to Bill and no one else got grapes. S2 says Sam also gave Rob grapes, which contradicts the restriction that only Bill received grapes. Therefore, it is a contradiction.

the prosodic focus is on "GRAPES"—this means that Rob only received grapes and did not get any other fruit (like bananas). S2 states Sam also gave Rob bananas, which deals with another type of fruit not mentioned or restricted in S1. It doesn’t contradict S1, but it’s not entailed either. Therefore, this is independent.
